/target
# Per-crate target dirs created when cargo runs scoped to a subcrate
# (e.g. `cargo test -p quanta-macros` from within the crate). The
# proc-macro's wasm-cache also lands here when CARGO_MANIFEST_DIR
# points at the crate rather than the workspace root.
crates/*/target/
# The grouped layout (crates/{gpu,lang,sci,ml,tools}/…) puts crates one
# level deeper; without this the per-crate target dirs are unignored.
# Deliberately-tracked files (the wasm kernel caches) override this,
# as before.
crates/*/*/target/
Cargo.lock
.cargo/config.toml
dist/
libopcodes_complete.rlib

# Verus side-effect build artifacts (`verus --crate-type=lib` drops
# .rlib files in the cwd of the verifier — they're not source).
# `just verus` redirects them to target/verus/; this catches stragglers
# from manual invocations.
/lib*.rlib

# Kani per-harness side-effect outputs (run from specs/verify/kani/).
specs/verify/kani/*.rlib
specs/verify/kani/*.out
specs/verify/kani/*.kani-metadata.json
specs/verify/kani/*.pretty_name_map.json
specs/verify/kani/*.type_map.json
specs/verify/kani/*.symtab.json
specs/verify/kani/*kani_metadata*

# Lean build artifacts (specs/verify/lean/)
specs/verify/lean/.lake/
specs/verify/lean/lib*.rlib
# Note: `specs/verify/lean/lake-manifest.json` is tracked so the
# mathlib pin is reproducible. Generated by `lake update` when
# dependencies change.

# B⁰ web glue build outputs — never committed (regenerated by
# `quanta build web` on every build). The `generated/` subdir is
# B′ codegen output that lands inside the example dir at stage time.
web/dist/
web/node_modules/
examples/web_add_one/*.js
examples/web_add_one/*.wasm
examples/web_add_one/generated/
examples/web_triangle/*.js
examples/web_triangle/*.wasm
examples/web_triangle/generated/
examples/web_textured/*.js
examples/web_textured/*.wasm
examples/web_textured/generated/
examples/web_diff/*.js
examples/web_diff/*.wasm
examples/web_diff/generated/

# Playwright headless smoke harness (B‴) artifacts.
web/test-results/
web/playwright-report/
web/playwright/.cache/
examples/*/target/

# Workspace-level content lives in the PARENT folder, not this repo.
# `roadmap/` (planning, design docs, dossiers) and `research/` (probes,
# audits) are part of the workspace, not Quanta — ignore any strays that
# get created under the repo root so they can't drift back into history.
/roadmap/
/research/
